From: Snow <sqlsnxw@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Example: set Snowfox as the default homepage

This is a STARTER EXAMPLE patch showing the format Snowfox uses. It changes
Firefox's default startup homepage preference. Delete or replace it with your
real customizations.

To create your own patches:
  1. cd work/firefox-<version>
  2. edit files
  3. git diff > ../../patches/0002-my-change.patch   (or use `diff -ruN`)

Patches are applied in sorted filename order with `patch -p1`.

diff --git a/browser/app/profile/firefox.js b/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
--- a/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
+++ b/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
@@ -1,3 +1,6 @@
+// Snowfox: example customization
+pref("browser.startup.homepage", "about:home");
+
 // This is the Firefox application preferences file. It is read once at startup
 // and the values are used to initialize preferences in the default branch.
 // Preferences set here are the default values.
